<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-04-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                    <head>No. 507.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Mathews</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-13"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 13,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 165.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 353, transmitting a copy of
                        the circular of the Moorish minister of foreign affairs relative to the
                        Sultan’s desire that Moorish subjects naturalized in foreign countries shall
                        become amenable to Moorish jurisdiction, has been received, and I take
                        pleasure in informing you that your action thereunder, based upon the treaty
                        of September 16, 1836, between the governments of the United States of
                        America and Morocco, meets with entire approval.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>